An Act relative to direct primary care.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 32A of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official
2 Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following section:-
3 “Section 35. A carrier may not deny payment for any health care service covered under
4 an enrollee’s health plan based solely on the basis that the enrollee’s referral was made by a
5 provider who is not a member of the carrier’s provider network.”
